data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
This wizard will assist you in the creation and upload process of a DNN Platform instance on Microsoft Azure Cloud Services.
On the next steps, you must specify the configuration parameters for the instances, so you should be familiar with DNN running on Azure Cloud Services deployment architecture. If you have any doubt, please visit http://dnnazureaccelerator.codeplex.com/ for more information.
Click the Next button to begin the process.

data.name: label62.Text
data.value: Select the DNN version that you want to deploy into Azure or specify a custom Url. The zip file containing the DNN distribution package will be downloaded and unzipped directly from Azure (if you use custom, make sure to introduce a public Url).

data.name: label47.Text
data.value: Enabling Azure Connect allows you to connect from on-premise computers or other cloud instances. This is very useful for doing certain maintenance tasks on the roles like mapping the VHD drive on your local computer for updating the contents.

data.name: label65.Text
data.value: To enable SSL communications on your website (https protocol), you must specify the certificate that will binded to your website and all trusted root certificates associated with it. Make sure you include all the certificates in the certification path to make your site certificate valid.

data.name: label38.Text
data.value: Enabling remote management options allows you to connect to all roles via RDP, FTP or Web Deploy. This is very useful for doing certain maintenance tasks on the roles and connecting directly to the site contents through WebMatrix.
